{"id":139970,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8xMzk5NzA=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/139970","title":"JIRA account misconfig causes internal info leak","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2016-05-20T16:35:14.824Z","submitted_at":"2016-05-20T16:35:14.824Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"kamil_hism","url":"/kamil_hism","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/005/311/834a58ff0f4a82db11ee6fe0e38772150ea735f7_original.jpg/3afcb5c896247e7ee8ada31b1c1eb8657e22241f911093acfe4ec7e97a3a959a"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":17011,"url":"https://hackerone.com/newrelic","handle":"newrelic","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/017/011/eba06abb23bd6c9c7d719ddafb9fa83bd2d66aaa_original./3afcb5c896247e7ee8ada31b1c1eb8657e22241f911093acfe4ec7e97a3a959a","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/017/011/eba06abb23bd6c9c7d719ddafb9fa83bd2d66aaa_original./eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"profile":{"name":"New Relic","twitter_handle":"newrelic","website":"https://newrelic.com","about":"New Relic's Coordinated Disclosure Program"}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2017-03-20T01:41:19.208Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-02-18T01:41:08.049Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"This issue was originally reported via email security@newrelic.com\n___\n\nHello,\n\nIn preparation for security conference I'm doing a research of popular task tracking systems / project management software and how they affect company's IT security.\n\nDuring investigation I've found several critical vulnerabilities in PM systems themselves and also identified over 200 misconfigured JIRA, Redmine, etc accounts. A bunch of them are Fortune 500 companies. They were all notified and almost everyone have already been fixed.\n\n# Issue\n\nIssue with NewRelic's account is a bit similar to http://www.geek.com/games/valve-has-56-people-working-on-half-life-3-1572498/. It's occurs because of wrong permissions scheme and leads to leak of some sensitive data. Whether the user is logged in or not in JIRA applications he is able to see all shared filters and dashboards. Basically, the instance is externally exposed to non-logged users.\n\nThere were detected leaking of such internal information:\n\n* employees roles, upcoming milestones, secret project and features through JIRA filters / dashsboards\n\nPlease use urls below to review this leaks:\n\n* https://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ConfigurePortalPages!default.jspa?view=popular\n* https://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ManageFilters.jspa?filterView=search\u0026Search=Search\u0026filterView=search\u0026sortColumn=favcount\u0026sortAscending=false\n\n# Resolution\n\nAnalyse each specific Filter or Dashboard shared with everyone by looking for \"Shared with all users\", in the \"Manage Filters\" and \"Manage Dashboards\" sections, and grant permissions to specific groups.\n\nThanks.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eThis issue was originally reported via email \u003ca title=\"security@newrelic.com\" href=\"mailto:security@newrelic.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003esecurity@newrelic.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHello,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn preparation for security conference I\u0026#39;m doing a research of popular task tracking systems / project management software and how they affect company\u0026#39;s IT security.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDuring investigation I\u0026#39;ve found several critical vulnerabilities in PM systems themselves and also identified over 200 misconfigured JIRA, Redmine, etc accounts. A bunch of them are Fortune 500 companies. They were all notified and almost everyone have already been fixed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch1 id=\"issue\"\u003eIssue\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIssue with NewRelic\u0026#39;s account is a bit similar to \u003ca title=\"http://www.geek.com/games/valve-has-56-people-working-on-half-life-3-1572498/\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.geek.com%2Fgames%2Fvalve-has-56-people-working-on-half-life-3-1572498%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://www.geek.com/games/valve-has-56-people-working-on-half-life-3-1572498/\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. It\u0026#39;s occurs because of wrong permissions scheme and leads to leak of some sensitive data. Whether the user is logged in or not in JIRA applications he is able to see all shared filters and dashboards. Basically, the instance is externally exposed to non-logged users.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere were detected leaking of such internal information:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eemployees roles, upcoming milestones, secret project and features through JIRA filters / dashsboards\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlease use urls below to review this leaks:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ConfigurePortalPages!default.jspa?view=popular\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewrelic.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2FConfigurePortalPages%21default.jspa%3Fview%3Dpopular\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ConfigurePortalPages!default.jspa?view=popular\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ManageFilters.jspa?filterView=search\u0026amp;Search=Search\u0026amp;filterView=search\u0026amp;sortColumn=favcount\u0026amp;sortAscending=false\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewrelic.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2FManageFilters.jspa%3FfilterView%3Dsearch%26Search%3DSearch%26filterView%3Dsearch%26sortColumn%3Dfavcount%26sortAscending%3Dfalse\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://newrelic.atlassian.net/secure/ManageFilters.jspa?filterView=search\u0026amp;Search=Search\u0026amp;filterView=search\u0026amp;sortColumn=favcount\u0026amp;sortAscending=false\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch1 id=\"resolution\"\u003eResolution\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnalyse each specific Filter or Dashboard shared with everyone by looking for \u0026quot;Shared with all users\u0026quot;, in the \u0026quot;Manage Filters\u0026quot; and \u0026quot;Manage Dashboards\u0026quot; sections, and grant permissions to specific groups.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThanks.\u003c/p\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":18,"name":"Information Disclosure"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2017-03-20T01:41:08.133Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-119242003.25361793,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":7,"voters":["delimitry","spam404","k3ypt0","eveeez","realtess","spetr0x","adsence771"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom